New York Rep. Eliot Engel, the top Democrat on the House Foreign Affairs Committee, is facing two primary challengers whose newly launched campaigns feature a number of progressive policy priorities.
He is campaigning against Engel’s foreign policy record and what he calls a “history of militarism” at a time when communities in his district were suffering.